TY  - JOUR
AB  - Most investment expenditures are irreversible. The firm invests until the full value of an incremental unit of capacity equals its full cost. The former includes the value of the option to not utilize the unit; the latter includes the opportunity cost of sinking resources in the unit. We examine implications for capacity choice, utilization, firm value, and long-run marginal cost. With irreversibility, capacity is smaller, and firm value can be largely attributable to growth possibilities.
